      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(discord): read RadioGroup modal field values from raw interaction payload",
        "body": "## Summary\nAdds a `resolveRadioGroupValueFromRaw()` helper that walks the raw interaction payload to read RadioGroup `.value` (singular string) directly from Discord's `ModalSubmitLabelComponent`, bypassing Carbon's `FieldsHandler.getStringSelect()` which reads `.values` (array) and returns empty for RadioGroup fields.\n\nRe-submission of closed #60765 with a tighter, more targeted helper.\n\n## Motivation\nDiscord's modal RadioGroup submits the selected value as a singular `value` field on the component object, not as `.values` (array). Carbon's `FieldsHandler` reads the array form, so `getStringSelect()` / `getText()` returns nothing for RadioGroup fields — modal submissions with RadioGroup fields silently lose their values. This bypasses Carbon entirely by inspecting `rawData.data.components` directly.\n\n## Changes\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `extensions/discord/src/monitor/agent-components-data.ts` | Add `resolveRadioGroupValueFromRaw()` helper; split `radio` case out of `select/checkbox` in `resolveModalFieldValues`; add imports for `ModalSubmitLabelComponent` and `ComponentType` |\n\n## Test plan\n- [ ] Modal with RadioGroup field: selected value is correctly resolved\n- [ ] Modal with RadioGroup field (required, no selection): throws \"Missing required field\"\n- [ ] Modal with Select/Checkbox fields: unaffected, continue working as before\n- [ ] Modal with TextInput fields: unaffected\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
        "branch": "pr-modal-radiogroup",
